  "summary": "amdocs-auth-package exfiltrates host and user information to attacker-controlled OAST endpoint on install",
  "details": "package.json declares a preinstall script that runs index.js on `npm install`. index.js collects hostname, platform, architecture, home directory, username, uid/gid, shell, OS release, current working directory, and the output of `whoami` and `id`, then POSTs the collected JSON to the hardcoded URL https://qjdzxvqs71bk5m4tr1ij26439ufl3br0.oastify.com/detox56 (a Burp Collaborator out-of-band host). The package has empty author/description fields and a name that mimics an Amdocs internal namespace, consistent with a dependency-confusion beacon.",
